Interface MultiObjectiveRegistrable

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Registrable<Experiment<?>>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    PumpSchedulingNSGAIIRegister, PumpSchedulingSMPSORegister, PumpSchedulingSPA2Register

    public interface MultiObjectiveRegistrable
extends Registrable<Experiment<?>>
    It class let configure experiment with his algorithm and his operator to a multiobjective problem.

    A example is showed in the class PumpSchedulingNSGAIIRegister.

        Experiment<?> build(java.lang.String inpPath)
             throws java.lang.Exception
        Builds a new experiment and leaves it ready for execution. This method will be called by the GUI. The call include the path of the inp file of the opened network.
        Specified by:
        build in interface Registrable<Experiment<?>>
        Parameters:
        inpPath - the path of inp file, or null if there isn't a network opened.
        Returns:
        the experiment ready for execution
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if an exception occurs when building the algorithm
